==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈʧɛkmeɪt/}}, {{SAMPA|/"tSEkmeIt/}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fa}} {{fa-Arab|[[شاه مات]]}} (shah mat), ''the king is dead'' or ''the king is conquered'' (borrowed through Middle English [[chekmat]], through Old French [[eschec mat]]).

===Interjection===
'''checkmate'''

# {{chess}} Word called out by the [[victor]] when making the conclusive move.

